The paper focuses on evaluating the planning and control aspects of robotic in-hand manipulation systems, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of object surface mesh from the YCB data-set suggests a possible application of computer vision (cs.CV) in the benchmark. The proposed metrics for measuring error in reaching the goal state may involve machine learning techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG). Finally, the evaluation results may involve system-level analysis and optimization, which falls under the field of control systems (cs.SY).
